Medical malpractice cases are among the most complex in personal injury law. They require medical expertise, meticulous evidence gathering, and the willingness to go up against well-funded hospital defense teams.

Troy Flake's federal prosecution background means he's built a career around complex cases with high evidentiary standards. He applies that same rigor to medical malpractice — working with medical experts, reviewing records, and building cases that stand up to aggressive defense tactics.
